it's Jeff bar here at AWS in Seattle
here's a few launches that caught my eye
this week AWS elastic beanstalk now
supports creating applicational
balancers to the console before this
update you can only create an
application load bouncer using the SDKs
or the CLI now you can choose
applicational bouncer in addition to
classic load balancer when you configure
your environment in the console Amazon
ElastiCache for Redis now provides a new
metric engine CPU utilization the new
metric provides more precise visibility
into the load of the Redis process
itself Amazon work Mail now allows you
to share mailboxes among your team
members all users that have been granted
access to a shared mailbox can send and
receive emails using this mailbox
without manually sharing access
credentials ship mailboxes make it easy
to use email addresses that need to be
monitored and used by teams Amazon's
simple notification service now supports
AWS private link this feature keeps your
messages within your VPC instead of
traversing the Internet thanks for
joining us this week for some of our
launch highlights for the full slate of
